	<text>
		<body>
			<p><pb facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006"/> <metamark>7</metamark></p>
			<p>little way into the intricate, profound <lb/> heart <metamark>^</metamark><add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_add-where" hand="metadata#HM" place="above">where</add> <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_delete-where" hand="metadata#HM">where</del> they originated. And we see, that <lb/> suffering, <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_delete-at" hand="metadata#HM">at</del> some time or other <metamark>^</metamark><add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_add-andin.." hand="metadata#HM" place="above">and in some shape or other,--</add> <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_delete-inhimflef" hand="metadata#HM">in himself</del><lb/>this only can enable any man to depict it in <lb/>others. All over <metamark>^</metamark><add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_add-him" hand="metadata#HM" place="above">him</add>, Hawthorne's melancholy rests <lb/>like an Indian Summer, which though bathing a whole country <lb/> <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_delete-uponhim" hand="metadata#HM">upon him</del> in one softness, still reveals the distinctive <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_delete-features and" hand="metadata#HM">features and</del> hue of <metamark>^</metamark><add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_add-every" hand="metadata#HM" place="above">every</add> <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_delete-each" hand="metadata#HM">each</del> towering hill, <metamark>-&gt;</metamark><add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_add-andeach" hand="metadata#HM" place="margin">and each </add>far-winding vale.</p>
			<p><metamark>[</metamark>But it is the least part of genius <lb/> that attracts admiration. Where Hawthorne is <lb/> known, he seems to be <metamark>^</metamark><add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_add-deemed" hand="metadata#HM" place="above">deemed</add> <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_delete-recognizedas" hand="metadata#HM">recognized as</del> a pleasant <lb/> writer, with a pleasant style, --a sequestered, <lb/> harmless man, from whom any deep and <lb/> weighty thing would <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_delete-be" hand="metadata#HM">be</del> <metamark>^</metamark><add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_add-hardlybeanticipated" hand="metadata#HM" place="above">hardly be anticipated: --</add> <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_delete-allbutentirelyunlookedfor" hand="metadata#HM">all but entirely unlooked for</del> <metamark>^</metamark><add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_add-amanwhomeansnomeaning" hand="metadata#HM" place="above">a man who means no meanings.</add> <lb/> But there is no man, in <add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_add-whom" hand="metadata#HM" place="above">whom</add> humor and love, <lb/> like mountain peaks, soar to such a rapt height, <lb/> as to receive the irradiations of the upper <lb/> skies; -- <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_-delete-inotherwords" hand="metadata#HM">in other words</del> there is no man in <lb/> whom humor and love are developed in that <lb/> high form called genius; no such man can exist <lb/> without also possessing, as the <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_delete-uponthetable" hand="metadata#HM">upon the table</del> <add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_add-indispensablecomplement" hand="metadata#HM" place="above">indispensable complement </add><lb/> of <add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_add-these" hand="metadata#HM" place="above">these</add> <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_delete-this" hand="metadata#HM">this</del>, a great, deep intellect, which drops down <lb/> into <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_delete-tho" hand="metadata#HM">tho</del> <add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_add-the" hand="metadata#HM" place="above">the</add> universe like a <metamark>^</metamark><add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_add-plummet" hand="metadata#HM" place="above">plummet</add> <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_delete-plamet" hand="metadata#HM">plamet</del>. <del change="metadata#StA" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_delete-love" hand="metadata#HM">Love</del> <metamark>^</metamark><add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_add-OrLove" hand="metadata#HM" place="above">Or, love</add> and humor <lb/>are only the eyes, through which such an intellect <lb/> views this world. The great beauty in such a <lb/> mind is but the product of its strength. What, <lb/> to all readers, can be more charming than the <lb/>piece entitled "Monsieur du Miroir"; and to <lb/> a <metamark>^</metamark><add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_add-reader" hand="metadata#HM" place="above">reader</add> <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_delete-reader" hand="metadata#HM">reader</del> at all capable of <metamark>^</metamark><add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json#f006_add-fully" hand="metadata#HM" place="above">fully</add> fathoming it, what, at the <lb/> same time, can possess more mystical depth <lb/>of meaning?--Yes, there he sits, and looks at me,--<lb/>this "shape of mystery," this "identical Monsieur du Miroir."</p>
